INSTALL
=======

To build from source, run the following commands from the top level
directory.

If you are building from repository code then first create the configure
script (if you are building from the source or binary package files then
skip this command as the configure script is included)

   autoreconf -v -i -W all

Now build the program

   ./configure
   make

After a successful build the 'dome' executable will be in the 'src'
directory. Copy it to where you want it manually, or optionally install
it with

   make install


Note: source and binary packages are available from

   https://www.antiprism.com/other/dome/


